   "body" : "Context: [C and C++ locale assumptions in bitcoind and bitcoin-qt](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/18124)\r\n\r\nAdd fuzzing harness for locale independence testing of functions in `strencodings.h` and `tinyformat.h`.\r\n\r\nThe tested functions (`ParseInt32(â¦)`, `ParseInt64(â¦)`, `atoi(const std::string&)`, `atoi64(const std::string& str)`, `i64tostr(const char*)`, `itostr(â¦)`, `strprintf(â¦)`) all call locale dependent functions (such as `strtol(â¦)`, `strtoll(â¦)`, `atoi(const char*)`, etc.) but are assumed to do so in a way that the tested functions return same results regardless of the chosen C locale (`setlocale`).\r\n\r\nThis fuzzer aims to test that those assumptions hold up also in practice now and over time.",
